        <h2>Discover Andhra Pradesh</h2>
        <p>Andhra Pradesh is a state in southeastern India, rich in culture, history, and natural beauty. Known for its ancient temples, stunning beaches, and diverse traditions, Andhra Pradesh is an exciting destination for anyone looking to experience India’s deep heritage.</p>

        <h3>Key Highlights</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Capital City:</strong> Amaravati</li>
            <li><strong>Official Language:</strong> Telugu</li>
            <li><strong>Major Festivals:</strong> Ugadi (Telugu New Year), Sankranti (Harvest Festival), and Dussehra (Festival of Victory)</li>
            <li><strong>Famous Temples:</strong> Tirumala Venkateswara Temple, Kanaka Durga Temple</li>
            <li><strong>Famous Cuisine:</strong> Andhra Biriyani, Gongura Pachadi, Pesarattu (a kind of pancake made from green gram)</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Popular Tourist Attractions</h3>
        <p>Andhra Pradesh offers a mix of spiritual, cultural, and natural wonders. Here are some of the must-visit places:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Tirupati:</strong> Home to the famous <em>Tirumala Venkateswara Temple</em>, one of the most visited pilgrimage sites in the world.</li>
            <li><strong>Visakhapatnam:</strong> A beautiful coastal city with serene beaches, including the famous <em>Ramakrishna Beach</em>.</li>
            <li><strong>Amaravati:</strong> The proposed capital city, known for its Buddhist heritage and the <em>Amaravati Stupa</em>.</li>
            <li><strong>Araku Valley:</strong> A scenic hill station known for its coffee plantations and lush greenery.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Culture and Heritage</h3>
        <p>Andhra Pradesh has a vibrant culture that blends classical arts and folk traditions. It is famous for Kuchipudi, one of the major classical dance forms of India. The state also has a rich tradition of Carnatic music and sculpture.</p>

